race.comment: INCANTATA (6) finished fourth two runs back at Canberra then improved last time out when a slick winner over 1460m at Queanbeyan. Must raise the bar but this looks well within her grasp. BILL PEYTO (5) tough old gelding who gets weight relief again on the backup. Big jump in class and trip when a plugging sixth over 2100m at Orange. This is his pet distance, and he can find the winners' list. HASIME (9) back in form after running on at her last two outings over this trip. Well drawn again with the claim and expected to figure prominently. NAPOLI (11) well drawn for this and assess on his good third at Cowra three runs back. Deep into the prep and stays in the mix.
